replacement_value: Sanctuary assists homeless individuals find housing and employment.
Youth in Focus programs provide pathways for low-income young people to rebuild their lives and community through work and education.
Example City Food for Charities acquires in-date food that would otherwise be wasted and works with local organisations to redistribute food to vulnerable communities.
The Example City Famly Project provides inclusive community based family therapy for the citizens of Example City.

Provision of services for older people in their homes to allow them to continue living in their communities with dignity. Serivices include:
  • Personal Care
  • Cleaning
  • Shopping
Example City Carnival Bay provides free and low-cost spaces for art therapy projects designed to help those with mental health needs.

The charity's provides support for students and teachers in Example City on matters that interfere with education by providing meals, laundry, legal advice and other facilities to keep students learning and support teaching staff.
Associated Parks is part of the Example City Town Hall, providing access to green spaces within the city for therapeutic and heallthy living programs.
Example House League of Friends provides hot meals at soup kitchens throughout Example City for anyone in need.
The Example Cross Trust distributes care packages to the most vulnerable in Example City and provides safe spaces for personal care such as laundry and bathing.
The Never Homeless Helpline refers any persons without access to housing to services within Example City. Services are first come, first serve. Due to demand, there may be a waiting list.

Young Minds program helps young people complete their high school education, preparing them for lifelong success with mentorship, funding and community support. Our engagement with the students begins with an evaluation to provide each young person with a personalised program for success.
A service to collect and report on in-date food from grocery stores within Example City limits, allowing stores to benefit from city-funded tax breaks as well as helping to feed those in need.
A pay-as-you-feel training program for nonprofit organisations perparing or seeking to prepare food within Example City.
Provides support for family and friends of people with a drinking problem.
Provides assisted social shopping for the elderly with twice weekly bus services and assistance provided by volunteers. This service is heavily subscribed and waiting period may apply.

Carnival Bay provides summer camp sessions for residents of Example City. Summer camp activities include: arts & crafts, field trips, indoor activities, outdoor games, free swim lessons, and swimming.

The skills refresh offers teaching staff in Example City free refresher courses in
  • Digital Skills
  • Childhood Development
  • Languages: Spanish

Parks Disability Service works to make Example City parks and their recreation programs accessible to persons with disabilities, removing architectural barriers and creating special programs for the disabled, such as wheelchair tennis, quad rugby, and beep baseball.
The Soup Kitchen operates seven days a week, 365 days a year. It serves two hot meals per day.

Meals To-Go at The Cross provides a bag lunch on a pay-as-you-can basis. Donors can buy a healthy bag lunch and donate a bag lunch to anyone in need of a meal. For a pre-paid meal, please take a prepaid slip from our "Feed the City" wall.

Provides dignity for our homeless citizens with a free, clean place to shower and take care of personal needs. Stalls are lockable for privacy and safety. A caretaker is available at all times.This service is supported by matched donations from City Hall.
Bubbles At The Cross provides low-cost and pay-as-you-can services to anyone needing laundry services in Example City.
